Rating: 4
A great seasonal hors d'oeuvre for fresh, Niagara peaches. I used pepper Boursin cheese instead of the ricotta, imported Italian honey and prosciutto, and finished with chopped chives. I also used french baguette for the crostini, sliced on the bias. Everybody loved them.

